<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/497: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-29T22:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 29,
                                            1919, 10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.46 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>3387. American Mission’s 2863, June 28th, 10 p.m., and 2044 [<hi rend="italic">2924</hi>], July 2. Senator Eliodoro Yanez of
                                Chile now states that recent change of Government in Peru causes him
                                to postpone the visit he intended making to Washington for the
                                purpose of discussing Tacna-Arica matter. He expects to stay in
                                France through August and will then probably return to Chile.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">American
                                Mission</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>